BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:k74OsCXc75EroTvqQAF8K
SUMMARY:History Café: Field Notes Podcast
DTSTAMP:20260325T062626Z
DTSTART:20260520T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join HistoryLink’s Tony Williams for a live recording of the Fi
	eld Notes podcast featuring UW Architecture Professor Vikram Prakash. We’r
	e digging into the intersection of deep time and urban design to discover 
	how Seattle’s geological past continues to shape its future. \\nHistory Ca
	fé is produced as a partnership between HistoryLink\\\, The Pacific Northw
	est Historians Guild\\\, and MOHAI. \\nASL Interpretation and CART caption
	ing are available during the program. In addition\\\, a limited number of 
	Assistive Listening Devices are available upon request. For more accessibi
	lity support\\\, email programs@mohai.org before the program. \\nGrab some
	 food for thought–complimentary snacks and beverages will be provided. \\n
	If you can’t make it to the museum\\\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube c
	hannel to virtually attend this event.\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/history-
	cafe-field-notes-podcast/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-field-notes-podcast/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\
	\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_FzHYzRBPrmQeXHnT87qh
SUMMARY:Drawing From History: Ripples of Time
DTSTAMP:20260325T062626Z
DTSTART:20260530T130000Z
DESCRIPTION:Lake Union is haunted by ghosts of the past\\\, echoing through
	 time. In this class\\\, participants will explore past\\\, present\\\, an
	d future of the Lake Union Watershed by creating quick layered gesture dra
	wings in charcoal\\\, based off photos and ephemera from MOHAI’s collectio
	ns. The class will culminate at the water’s edge\\\, creating a drawing re
	presenting visions for the future. \\nDrawing From History is offered in p
	artnership with Gage Academy of Art. \\nAll art making materials will be p
	rovided. Tickets include access to MOHAI’s exhibitions. For accessibility 
	support and general program inquiries\\\, email programs@mohai.org.\n\nhtt
	ps://mohai.org/event/drawing-from-history-ripples-of-time/\n\nFrom MOHAI -
	 Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/drawing-from-history-ripples-of-time/
LOCATION:Microsoft Lakefront Pavilion\\\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seatt
	le\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6Q-uJ6T7irS2Hf9Sm5Yfx
SUMMARY:Unpaving SODO Walking Tour
DTSTAMP:20260325T062626Z
DTSTART:20260612T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:What does SODO mean to you? Industrial space\\\, maybe sports\\
	\, perhaps a no-man’s land between Pioneer Square’s nightlife and the citi
	es further south. How do we even define this territory south of downtown w
	here the Duwamish watershed meets the Puget Sound? A liminal space that be
	gan with the natural foundation of tidal flats and the flow of a river. An
	 urban landscape that has been literally built on the dreams of manifest d
	estiny. It has been occupied and enjoyed by the commercial minded and marg
	inalized alike – those pushing boundaries and those enforcing them. \\nJoi
	n Invisible Histories on a 1-mile immersive guided walking tour of the cit
	yscape you pass daily but never truly see. Storytelling\\\, history and th
	eatrical elements will enliven these spaces known as SODO. Guests will uni
	quely experience the past\\\, from the untold stories of Seattle’s evolvin
	g landscapes and industries\\\, to the hidden histories of the depression 
	era Hooverville\\\, all the way to the energetic underground club scene of
	 the 1990s. Explore the layers beneath the pavement while we bring history
	 to life like never before! \\nThis tour requires walking between multiple
	 sites in SODO. For any accessibility support\\\, or general inquiries\\\,
	 email programs@mohai.org.\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/unpaving-sodo-walkin
	g-tour/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/unpaving-sodo-walking-tour/
LOCATION:Offsite
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mC8qVFyW2re1XVKbFzDBc
SUMMARY:History Café: Shelf Life Community Story Project
DTSTAMP:20260325T062626Z
DTSTART:20260617T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Shelf Life Community Story Project records oral histories w
	ith current and former residents of Seattle’s Central District neighborhoo
	d. Join contributors for a talk about their new book\\\, Limitless: Storie
	s from the Neighborhood that Shaped Seattle\\\, the culmination of a multi
	-year oral history project in Seattle’s historically redlined Central Dist
	rict neighborhood. Stories of innovation\\\, interdependence\\\, self-dete
	rmination\\\, creativity\\\, and resistance are illustrated by seven artis
	ts with roots in the CD. \\nHistory Café is produced as a partnership betw
	een HistoryLink\\\, The Pacific Northwest Historians Guild\\\, and MOHAI. 
	\\nASL Interpretation and CART captioning are available during the program
	. In addition\\\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are avai
	lable upon request. For more accessibility support\\\, email programs@moha
	i.org before the program. \\nGrab some food for thought–complimentary snac
	ks and beverages will be provided. \\nIf you can’t make it to the museum\\
	\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to virtually attend this even
	t.\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-shelf-life-community-story-proj
	ect/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-shelf-life-community-story-project
	/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\
	\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
